ertaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":24,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William de Bromhall was born in 1235, in Broomhall, Cheshire, England as the son of John De Bromehall. He had at least 2 sons with Mrs. William Bromhall. He died in 1285, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1235–1285":"1235–1285","1222–Female":"1222–Surnud","1265–1315":"1265–1315","1285–1345":"1285–1345","1205–1255":"1205–1255","1205":"1205","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1235":"1235","1345":"1345","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","abt. 1255":"umbes 1255","Bromhall":"Broomhall, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bromhall, Cheshire, England":"Broomhall, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1235–1285":"1235–1285","1222–Female":"1222–Kuollut","1265–1315":"1265–1315","1285–1345":"1285–1345","1205–1255":"1205–1255","1205":"1205","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1235":"1235","1345":"1345","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","abt. 1255":"noin 1255","Bromhall":"Broomhall, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bromhall, Cheshire, England":"Broomhall, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"1235–1285":"1235–1285","1222–Female":"1222–Décédée","1265–1315":"1265–1315","1285–1345":"1285–1345","1205–1255":"1205–1255","1205":"1205","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1235":"1235","1345":"1345","1255":"1255","1222":"1222","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","abt. 1255":"environ 1255","Bromhall":"Broomhall, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bromhall, Cheshire, England":"Broomhall, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William de Bromha